<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Build Up Noted Around Cuito </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1101081694 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1101081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While one waits for peace from Lusaka, in Angola the 
war continues. Over the weekend, National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] rebels strengthened their 
positions in the outlaying areas of the city of Cuito, Bie 
Province. Local sources say UNITA reinforcements have come from 
Soyo. UNITA plans to mount a large-scale attack on the city of 
Bie. 
  Savimbi's men have attacked the town of Limbombos in Bengo 
Province, and Quijenje and Ukuma in Huambo Province. UNITA's 
heavy artillery fire caused a substantial number of dead and 
wounded among civilians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

