<F P=101> Kenya </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Returns From Israel, Comments on Trip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1201222694 Nairobi Kenya Broadcasting Corporation Network 
in English 1600 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1201222694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi Kenya Broadcasting Corporation Network 
in English 1600 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] His Excellency President Daniel arap Moi today 
said Kenya can tremendously benefit from the advanced technology 
and farming methods practiced in Israel to forge ahead in 
agriculture. The president particularly noted that Israel had a 
lot to offer to Kenya in terms of irrigation to convert arid 
land into rich farmland. President Moi said it was his first 
time to visit Israel and pointed that he was very impressed by 
the patriotism of Israelis and their efforts that have 
transformed their nation from a desert to a green rich farmland. 
[passage omitted] 
  President Moi extended greetings from Israel to Kenyans and 
announced that Kenya will send an ambassador to Israel this 
month. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

