Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Jan 13 SAPA -- Political leaders 
aligned to the African National Congress [ANC]-led Patriotic 
Front [PF] met in Johannesburg on Thursday to formulate a joint 
election strategy. 
  The PF leaders included ANC President Nelson Mandela, Labour 
Party leader Allan Hendrickse, Transvaal Indian Congress 
representative Cassim Saloojee and the leaders of Lebowa, Venda, 
Transkei and kwaNdebele. PF co-ordinator Ismael Ibrahim said 
the purpose of the meeting was to discuss the April 27 elections 
