<H3> <TI>   Afewerki, PRC Delegation Meet, Note Bilateral Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1401113094 Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea in 
Tigrinya 0400 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1401113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tigrinya </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Isayas Afewerki yesterday afternoon met 
and held talks with the Chinese delegation led by Mr. Qian 
Qichen, the PRC deputy prime minister and foreign minister. 
During the talks, President Isayas Afewerki and Mr. Qian Qichen 
extensively discussed bilateral relations between Eritrea and 
China and ways and means of resolving the conflicts in the Horn 
of Africa. The two sides noted that the solutions to the 
current economic problems facing Africa are dependent on 
regional and continental cooperation. Meanwhile Mr. Qian Qichen 
extended Chinese President Jiang Zemin's invitation to President 
Isayas Afewerki to undertake an official visit to China. 
[passage omitted] 

