<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IFP Spokesman Clarifies Buthelezi's 13 Jan Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1301192594 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 1800 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1301192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] said it would 
continue negotiations with the ANC [African National Congress] 
for as long as it was worth doing so. Clarifying a speech 
delivered by Dr. Mangosuthu Buthelezi yesterday, in which he 
said the IFP and the KwaZulu government should reconsider 
further talks with the ANC, the IFP's Dr. Ziba Jiyane said this 
wasn't a call to pull out of talks with the ANC. He also said a 
decision on whether the IFP should participate in the elections 
or not would be made when the party met at the end of the month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

