Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following the head of state's message of 14 January, 
several political parties have been analyzing it. The Chistian 
Democrats Party's [PDC] interim chairman, Boboliko, chaired a 
meeting over the weekend. After the meeting Vice Chairman 
(Mbesi Mbenatubi) spoke to reporters. He told reporters that no 
son of Zaire can any longer take it upon himself alone to decide 
for the country. According to Mr. Mbenatubi, one cannot stand 
on the signing of a draft protocol agreement to dissolve the 
High Council of the Republic, which emanated from the sovereign 
national conference. 

