<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Says Cuban `Mercenaries' in Cuanza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1801055494 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1900 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1801055494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a communique received at our news desk this 
afternoon, through our correspondent Morais Abel, the military 
command of the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola [FALA] 
in the Cuanza Norte Military Region has reported the presence in 
Cambambe and Dondo of a large number of well-equipped Cuban and 
Katanguese mercenaries. According to the communique, these 
forces, acting jointly with the People's Armed Forces for the 
Liberation of Angola and the riot police, have the mission of 
occupying all areas under control of the National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] in Cuanza Norte, 
particularly the city of Ndalatando, the provincial capital. 
The FALA military command said the mercenaries [words 
indistinct] will not find a room for maneuvers and will be 
repulsed. The military command has warned the international 
community of the danger that this Eduardo dos Santos' adventure 
represents for the Angolan people and the ongoing peace talks in 
Lusaka. 

</TEXT>

