<H3> <TI>   Cultural Accord Protocol Signed With Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1801075094 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1800 GMT 
14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1801075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Nigeria and Cuba, today in Lagos, signed the 
protocol for the implementation of the cultural and educational 
agreement between the two countries. Kobalakin Pong reports 
that the accord was signed on behalf of Nigeria by the minister 
of information and culture, Professor Jerry Gana, while the 
Cuban ambassador to Nigeria, Mr. Giraldo Mazola, initialed the 
document for his country. 
  [Begin Pong recording] The agreement on cultural and 
educational cooperation between Nigeria and Cuba was signed in 
1981. The accord, according to Prof. Gana, had brought more 
awareness of the benefits to be derived from closer economic, 
cultural, and educational cooperation between the two countries. 
[passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

