<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Criticizes Prime Minister's Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1801171594 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise in French 1115 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1801171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We start the news bulletin with the following 
last-minute piece of information: Major General Juvenal 
Habyarimana, the president of the Republic, said he was amazed 
at the words of Prime Minister Agathe Uwilingiyimana and those 
of the prime minister designate, Faustin Twagiramungu, words 
broadcast on Radio Rwanda on 16 and 17 January 1993, 
respectively. This is stated in a communique issued by the 
Office of the President of the Republic. 
  According to the communique, the head of state regretted 
that 
high-level leaders like them continue to make multi-faceted 
statements unlikely to help the establishment of the broad-based 
transitional institutions and described the statements as a show 
of force. 
  According to the same communique, the president said that it 
is (?inconceivable) that the country is ruled through 
communiques while there is another perfectly adequate way to 
rule the country: in the spirit of the fundamental law which 
recommends consultations within the Council of Ministers. 
  The communique, which reached us today, is signed by the 
principal private secretary of the president of the Republic, 
Enoch Ruhigira. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-43888 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr012_a_94002" </HT>


