<H3> <TI>   PAC Regional Leader Objects To Suspending Armed Struggle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1901073194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2029 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1901073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Umtata Jan 18 SAPA -- The Pan Africanist Congress 
[PAC] central Transkei region on Tuesday [18 January] expressed 
its shock and disgust at what it termed the PAC's unilateral 
decision, announced on Sunday, to suspend its armed struggle. 
PAC Regional Secretary Mfanelo Skwatsha said the move was not in 
line with national conference resolutions taken in Umtata last 
year. 
  "The conference mandated the PAC leadership to negotiate a 
mutual cessation of hostilities with the regime. This move is 
nothing but capitulation and renegation on the part of the PAC 
leadership," Mr Skwatsha said. 
  He called for a special conference for the PAC leadership to 
explain its decision. 

</TEXT>

