<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Withdraw </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2001100094 Paris AFP in English 0015 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2001100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kinshasa, 19 Jan (AFP) -- Zairian security forces 
have now withdrawn from around the home of opposition leader 
Etienne Tshisekedi after sealing off his residence during 
Wednesday morning, one of his close aides said. There has been 
no official explanation of why the troops surrounded 
Tshisekedi's Kinshasa home but the move appeared to be linked to 
a strike on Wednesday called by him to protest the dissolution 
last week by President Mobutu Sese Seko of the country's rival 
legislatures. Shops and most offices stayed closed and the 
capital's streets were virtually empty of traffic all day. 

</TEXT>

