<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   De Klerk, Mandela Sign Local Government Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2001140994 Umtata Capital Radio in English 1300 GMT 20 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2001140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Umtata Capital Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] ANC [African National Congress] leader Nelson 
Mandela and State President F. W. de Klerk have signed an 
agreement marking the restoration of legitimate local 
government. After addressing the local government summit at the 
World Trade Center outside Johannesburg, the two leaders and the 
2,200 delegates were presented with an agreement on finance, 
services, and service rendering. 
  The agreement recognizes the recently promulgated Local 
Government Transitional Act and commits signatories to promote 
and expedite the normalization of local government. It says the 
summit marks the start of restoring legitimacy and credibility 
to local government finance, services, and service rendering in 
particular. 
  Meanwhile, earlier in the day Mandela called for an end to 
the rent and services boycott. 

</TEXT>

