<H3> <TI>   Comments on ANC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2101063294 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2101063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President F.W. de Klerk got the National Party [NP] 
three-day election campaign in the Western Transvaal off the 
ground yesterday when he addressed two meetings at 
Potchefstroom. Mr. de Klerk was warmly received by an audience 
of mostly first-year students at the University of 
Potchefstroom. Taking the stage, he accused the African 
National Congress [ANC] of intolerance and intimidation. 
  [Begin de Klerk recording] The ANC has robbed hundreds of 
thousands, if you look back over the past ten years, of young 
black South Africans of a proper education by making a political 
battlefield of school education. They're a dangerous party, 
they're a reality, they're strong, they have substantial 
support, but there is only one party which can cut them down to 
size -- and they need to be cut down to size -- and that is the 
National Party. [end recording] 
  From the University Mr. de Klerk went to a meeting of 
National Party organizers at the Potchefstroom Hall. The road 
show continues this morning with meetings at Klerksdorp and 
Rustenburg. 

</TEXT>

