<H3> <TI>   Withdraws Threat To Stop Troop Confinement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2001153794 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1500 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2001153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Afonso Dhlakama, leader of the Mozambique National 
Resistance [Renamo], has withdrawn his warning that he would 
definitely cancel the confinement of his forces by 22 January 
should government troops continue to report to assembly points 
at a slow pace. Speaking in a telephone interview, the Renamo 
president said if his organization went ahead with the 
cancellation it would be helping Frelimo to continue making 
mistakes regarding the implementation of the General Peace 
Accord. Afonso Dhlakama said he felt disappointed with the slow 
pace at which government troops were reporting to assembly 
points, saying he has been under pressure from his generals and 
commanders who wish to know the reason for the executive's 
attitude. [as heard] The Renamo leader said, however, that the 
confinement of troops will continue. 

</TEXT>

