<H3> <TI>   Official Denies Government Obstacles to Renamo in Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2001141494 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1030 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2001141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gaza Provincial Governor Eugenio Numaio has 
described as unfounded the accusations made by Jose de Castro, 
Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] Foreign Affairs 
Department chief, that Renamo authorities are experiencing many 
difficulties because of the obstacles raised by provincial 
authorities. 
  On 14 January Jose de Castro granted an interview to Radio 
Mozambique in Xai-Xai during which he accused the Gaza 
Provincial Government in general, and Governor Eugenio Numaio in 
particular, of not even wanting to hear of Renamo in the 
province. He also said that the provincial government has not 
shown any interest in granting premises for the Renamo 
provincial branch to operate and to accommodate Renamo's three 
provincial advisers. 
  Gaza Provincial Governor Numaio noted that such accusations 
are typical of people who only know how to make demands and know 
little about the difficulties faced by those wanting to satisfy 
those needs. 

</TEXT>

