<H3> <TI>   Government Forces Mutiny in Magude 19 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2101084394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2101084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A police company assigned to the Nyanga Battalion 
stationed in Magude, Maputo Province, on 19 January took part in 
violent action, using AKM weapons and mortars. The media office 
of the Maputo Provincial Police Command told NOTICIAS that the 
troops were demanding payment of annual bonus for 1993. There 
are no reports of vandalism or deaths, but the use of weapons 
resulted in Magude residents abandoning the area. 

</TEXT>

