<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   High Council Endorses New Parliamentary Institution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2101121594 Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network in 
French 1900 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2101121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After the decision by the political class to set up 
a single chamber parliament based on the head of state's 
decision to allow the political class to reach a consensus on 
ending the dual parliamentarian institutions as well as other 
institutions of the Republic, the former High Council of the 
Republic [HCR] established by the Sovereign National Conference, 
has just agreed to endorse this new institution that will 
include all former deputies, former HCR members, and former 
advisors. During a special HCR session at the People's Palace, 
which was attended by 368 members, 223 voted for the decision 
while 80 voted against and 60 abstained. 
  As we can see, the political will expressed during the 
negotiations has finally prevailed and each participant has 
expressed his accord in line with his own views, sometimes with 
different words or different procedures. The main thing, 
however, is that the people have now understood and that the 
entire political class is driven by a single ideal, that of 
putting an end to dual Republican institutions, which is a happy 
prelude to fair and free elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

