<H3> <TI>   19 Jan Tuareg Attack in Mansou Leaves 7 Dead </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2101165094 Paris AFP in French 2121 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2101165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Niamey, 20 Jan (AFP) -- An attack carried out on 
19 January in the Mansou locality near Tahoua (400 km northeast 
of Niamey) by the Tuareg rebel movement left seven dead, 
including four rebels, Niger national radio reported yesterday 
evening. The three other victims were two gendarmes and a 
native of the village, the radio specified. It explained that 
the attack was directed at the Manzou market and that all the 
attackers, on whom "coded documents" were found, had been 
killed. The last deadly operation carried out by the Niger 
Tuaregs dates back to 7 February, when 30 people were killed at 
Tassara (530 km northeast of Niamey). [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

